The National Examinations Council yesterday released the June/July 2019 Senior School Certificate Examination results. It delisted 18 supervisors and de-recognised three schools in Katsina, Kebbi and Oyo States for two years for alleged involvement in malpractices. NECO Acting Registrar/Chief Executive, Abubakar Mohammed Gana, said officials alleged to have behaved contrary to expectations would face appropriate disciplinary measures if found guilty. OVER 5,000 NIGERIAN MEN HAVE  OVERCOME POOR BEDROOM PERFORMANCE SYNDROME DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY The analysis of performance by candidates shows that 984, 162, representing 85.50 percent got credit and above in English Language; while 954, 399 representing 83.03 percent, passed Mathematics. The analysis shows an increase of 0.11 percent in the number of candidates that passed both subjects compared to last year. However, there is a drop in number of candidates who made five credits and above irrespective of English language and mathematics. 68% pass NECO with credits in English, maths 68% pass NECO with credits in English, maths NECO records high cases of malpractices in Nov/Dec exams Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin